5: All right! Keep it goin', everyone!
9:
The Palace of Stars is sacred to the
Overlords. I doubt the Purgers will be
reckless with their attacks!
12:
Push on until we take the central
core!
24:
Can you at least TRY to keep up?! I
can't believe we used to be the
same person!
29:
...Moving one's arms and legs
independently is an advanced
technique...
40:
With everyone working together,
we've got this! Let's keep going!
45: There it is... I see the way in!
53: So... this is the core of the Palace?
58:
This is the dragon's power... I should
have known...
61:
When I gained my powers, I felt it—a
shining light, basking me in its
luminance.
63:
As though it was the very will of
some higher being...
68:
This power doesn't come from the
light... It's all an illusion!
73:
Exactly. It's been
manipulated—twisted and warped
to appear as a brilliant light.
79: Alk! Stella! Look at these things...
82: It never ends... It's always the same...
86:
...They're filled with people? And
everyone is sleeping...
88:
Are these... isolation tanks? Could
these people really be the Ov—
91: You must not disturb their slumber.
95:
Lay down your weapons. Discord
and bloodshed are not desired.
101:
You got some nerve spoutin' that
crap when YOU'RE the ones that
started the damn purge! SHOW
YOURSELF ALREADY!
105:
The Guardian serves and protects
the Palace of Stars. Newcomers,
discard your weapons.
115:
We've come to stop the Purgers. To
find a way to prevent the Abyss
from expanding and destroying
everything.
117:
Please, tell us what you know. We
need to understand...
121:
Why have you let things become like
this?
128:
The Guardian exists solely to provide
answers. Should you seek answers...
151:
What's the matter, Ayumu? You
were off in your own little world.
160:
What've you got there... A balloon
sword? Haha, that takes me back. I
remember taking a few whacks
from those...
163:
Anyway, it's time to eat. Can you put
that thing down and help get lunch
ready?
176:
Phew, I'm pooped! Why do we gotta
practice on the weekend anyway?!
Hey... Where's Mom?
180:
Last I saw, she was checking out the
tomatoes.
184:
Bad news, everyone! The whole
tomato patch is ruined...
188:
Awww. I told you they needed more
water, didn't I?
193:
It's fine. Our failures can teach us
what we did right and wrong.
202:
That's your cue, Yumu! I think an
omelet would perk Mom right back
up!
207: You just want one for yourself...
212:
Probably because you're better at
making them, son.
216: Well, Ayumu? Can we count on you?
224:
It's okay. There's no more need for
orders.
226:
You should know that already.
You've comforted the elves and
heard their song...
228:
Let's change this world... We'll make
it so no one has to kill another! We
can do it together...
229:
That's right. I've already shown you
that we don't need to fight.
